Overview

Client for the EVE Swagger Interface (ESI) API.

Defined Under Namespace

Modules: Alliance, Asset, Bookmark, Calendar, Character, Clone, Contact, Contract, Corporation, Dogma, FactionWarfare, Fitting, Fleet, Incursion, Industry, Insurance, Killmail, Location, Loyalty, Mail, Market, Opportunity, PlanetaryInteraction, Route, Search, Skill, Sovereignty, Status, Universe, UserInterface, Wallet, War

Constant Summary collapse

DEFAULT_BASE_URL = 
"https://esi.evetech.net"
DEFAULT_VERSION = 
"latest"
ERROR_MAPPING = 
{
  400 => ESI::Errors::BadRequestError,
  401 => ESI::Errors::UnauthorizedError,
  403 => ESI::Errors::ForbiddenError,
  404 => ESI::Errors::NotFoundError,
  420 => ESI::Errors::ErrorLimitedError,
  422 => ESI::Errors::UnprocessableEntityError,
  500 => ESI::Errors::InternalServerError,
  503 => ESI::Errors::ServiceUnavailableError,
  504 => ESI::Errors::GatewayTimeoutError,
  520 => ESI::Errors::EveServerError
}.freeze

Constructor Details

#initialize(user_agent:, base_url: DEFAULT_BASE_URL, version: DEFAULT_VERSION, cache: {}, instrumentation: {}, logger: nil) ⇒ Client

Returns a new ESI::Client.

See the faraday-http-cache documentation for information on how to set up caching via the cache parameter.

Parameters:

  • user_agent (String) —

    Value of the User-Agent header for HTTP calls

  • base_url (String) (defaults to: DEFAULT_BASE_URL) —

    The base URL of the ESI API

  • version (String) (defaults to: DEFAULT_VERSION) —

    The version of the ESI API

  • logger (Object) (defaults to: nil) —

    The logger to use

  • cache (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    The cache configuration to use

  • instrumentation (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    The instrumentation configuration to use

Options Hash (cache:):

  • :store (Object) —

    The cache store (e.g. Rails.cache)

  • :logger (Object) —

    The logger (e.g. Rails.logger)

  • :instrumenter (Object) —

    The instrumenter (e.g. ActiveSupport::Notifications)

Options Hash (instrumentation:):

  • :name (String) —

    The name to use for instrumentation

  • :instrumenter (Object) —

    The instrumenter to use (e.g. ActiveSupport::Notifications)

# File 'lib/esi/client.rb', line 110

def initialize(user_agent:, base_url: DEFAULT_BASE_URL, version: DEFAULT_VERSION, cache: {}, instrumentation: {}, logger: nil) # rubocop:disable Layout/LineLength, Metrics/ParameterLists
  @base_url = base_url
  @cache = cache
  @instrumentation = instrumentation
  @user_agent = user_agent
  @version = version
  @logger = logger
end

#get_character_calendar(character_id:, from_event: nil, headers: {}, params: {}) ⇒ Object Also known as: get_characters_character_id_calendar Originally defined in module Calendar

Get 50 event summaries from the calendar. If no from_event ID is given, the resource will return the next 50 chronological event summaries from now. If a from_event ID is specified, it will return the next 50 chronological event summaries from after that event.

This endpoint is cached for up to 5 seconds.

This endpoint requires authorization (see ESI::Client#authorize).

    An EVE character ID

  • from_event (Integer) (defaults to: nil) —

#get_character_calendar_raw(character_id:, from_event: nil, headers: {}, params: {}) ⇒ Object Originally defined in module Calendar

Get 50 event summaries from the calendar. If no from_event ID is given, the resource will return the next 50 chronological event summaries from now. If a from_event ID is specified, it will return the next 50 chronological event summaries from after that event.

This endpoint is cached for up to 5 seconds.

This endpoint requires authorization (see ESI::Client#authorize).

#get_markets_region_orders(region_id:, order_type: "all", type_id: nil, headers: {}, params: {}) ⇒ Object Also known as: get_markets_region_id_orders Originally defined in module Market

Return a list of orders in a region.

This endpoint is cached for up to 300 seconds.

Parameters:

  • region_id (Integer) —

    Return orders in this region

  • order_type (String) (defaults to: "all") —

    Filter buy/sell orders, return all orders by default. If you query without type_id, we always return both buy and sell orders. Must be one of: buy, sell, all

  • type_id (Integer) (defaults to: nil) —

    Return orders only for this type

  • params (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    Additional query string parameters

  • headers (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    Additional headers

Raises:

  • (ESI::Errors::BadRequestError) —

    Bad request

  • (ESI::Errors::NotFoundError) —

    Not found

#post(path, payload: {}, params: {}, headers: {}) ⇒ Object

Make a POST request to the ESI endpoint.

Parameters:

  • path (String) —

    The request path, excluding version like latest.

  • params (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    Query string parameters to pass to the request.

  • headers (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    Headers to pass to the request.

  • payload (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    Payload to encode as JSON to pass to the request.

# File 'lib/esi/client.rb', line 150

def post(path, payload: {}, params: {}, headers: {})
  make_request(:post, path, params: params, headers: headers, payload: payload)
end

#put(path, payload: {}, params: {}, headers: {}) ⇒ Object

Make a PUT request to the ESI endpoint.

Parameters:

  • path (String) —

    The request path, excluding version like latest.

  • params (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    Query string parameters to pass to the request.

  • headers (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    Headers to pass to the request.

  • payload (Hash) (defaults to: {}) —

    Payload to encode as JSON to pass to the request.

# File 'lib/esi/client.rb', line 160

def put(path, payload: {}, params: {}, headers: {})
  make_request(:put, path, params: params, headers: headers, payload: payload)
end
